description: The Gyeonggi-do Museum of Art, which opened in October 2006, uses a vibrant ecological lake as the background, and the front of the building is a bright glass structure. The museum displays and collects various works of domestic and foreign artists, and provides various cultural services such as research, education, and publicity. It can also hold professional, artistic, regional and global integration of various planning exhibitions.

The mountain in Gyesan-dong, Gyeyang-gu, Incheon Metropolitan City, is 395 meters high and is the highest city in Incheon Metropolitan City except Ganghwa Island. In Guiyang District, Jindalee blooms very much. After climbing to the top, all sides are suddenly bright, so you can see the surrounding islands such as Yeongjongdo and Ganghwado from the west, the panorama of Seoul special cities such as Gimpo Airport to the east, Goyang City to the north, and Incheon Metropolitan City to the south.
